Energex MineralsLtd said economic evaluation of reserves indicates high-gradeoperation from three open pits may be feasable based onfive-year operation at 100 tons a day, a payback of less than1-1/2 years.    An increase in the project's life, profitability and scaleis anticipated as additional reserves are developed in 1987,the company said.    Current reserves are one mln long tons at 0.20 ounce goldper ton, all categories; proven-probable 262,242 long tons at0.25 ounce gold per ton, the company said. Reuter&#3;